This file contains a detailed description of all the steps required to install the software. More importantly, it should contain the most up-to-date instructions on what software is required to run all aspects of the obs.


- Tested on Ubuntu 14.04

- Start by installing a few things that won't hurt and will be useful in the future.

sudo apt-get install emacs vim screen


- Firstly, clone the repository: 

sudo apt-get install git gitk
git clone https://jpsbento@code.google.com/p/macquarie-observatory-automation/ 

- Then, each of these sections refers to installing stuff necessary for aspects of running the obs

- General requirements:

IRAF/PyRAF is a requirement. At this time, the installation of UREKA contains also ipython and all the standard science/plotting/fits modules, so in one go, this can be done. The download is large (1GB) but will work.

- Go to ssb.stsci.edu/ureka/ Click on the latest version and download and run the installer in your home directory.
Change the .bashrc file to include the 'ur_setup' command at the end of the file. Restart terminal. NOw IRAF/PyRAF and all of python is installed.

- For serial communication with python: 

pip install pyserial


-----------------------------LABJACK------------------------

Exodriver (required for u3)
sudo apt-get install build-essential
sudo apt-get install libusb-1.0-0 libusb-1.0-0-dev
sudo apt-get install git-core
git clone git://github.com/labjack/exodriver.git
cd exodriver/
sudo ./install.sh

LABJACK PYTHON

git clone git://github.com/labjack/LabJackPython.git
cd LabJackPython/
sudo python setup.py install
cp Examples/EI1050/ei1050.py ~/Ureka/variants/common/lib/python2.7/site-packages/



--------------------INDI devices-------------------------

sudo apt-add-repository ppa:mutlaqja/ppa
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install indi-full

